Aŋpetu šakpe en Yehowa mahpiya, maka, miniwaŋća ka taku ohnaka ko owasíŋ kaǧa; Day six in Jehovah heaven, earth, water-all and what is-in also all made;

Gloss: Day six in Jehovah heaven, earth, water-all and what is-in also all made;

Translate this English sentence to Dakota:

In six days Jehovah made heaven, earth, all water and whatever is in them also;

Note: 'Mahpiya' = heaven/sky. 'Miniwaŋća' = water-all/all waters. 'Ohnaka' = is-in/contained. 'Kaǧa' = made.
